{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idbc17a4dd-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s2296b–2"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"2296b–2"},"text":"§ 2296b–2.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Sale of remaining DOE inventories","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The Secretary, after making the transfer required under section 2297c–6 ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"idref":"fn003285"},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"type":"footnote","id":"fn003285"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{},"text":"1","children":[],"tail":" See References in Text note below."}],"tail":" of this title, may sell, from time to time, portions of the remaining inventories of raw or low-enriched uranium of the Department that are not necessary to national security needs, to the Corporation, at a fair market price. Sales under this section may be made only if such sales will not have a substantial adverse impact on the domestic uranium mining industry. Proceeds from sales under this subsection shall be deposited into the general fund of the United States Treasury."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idbc17a4de-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/102/486/tX/s1013"},"text":"Pub. L. 102–486, title X, § 1013","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1992-10-24"},"text":"Oct. 24, 1992","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/106/2949"},"text":"106 Stat. 2949","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idbc17a4df-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idbc17a4e0-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idbc17a4e1-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t42/s2297c–6"},"text":"Section 2297c–6 of this title","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/104/134/tIII/s3116/a/1"},"text":"Pub. L. 104–134, title III, § 3116(a)(1)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1996-04-26"},"text":"Apr. 26, 1996","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/110/1321-349"},"text":"110 Stat. 1321–349","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"codification","id":"idbc17a4e2-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Codification","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Section was enacted as part of the Energy Policy Act of 1992, and not as part of the Atomic Energy Act of 1954 which comprises this chapter.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null}
